        <p>Instructions for command-line GPG users</p>
        <ul>
        <li>Use at your own risk. Comes with NO WARRANTY, express or implied.</li>
        <li>If you know how to sign with GPG, you can do that:<br>
            <tt>gpg [--default-key john] --clearsign [file.txt]</tt><br>
            (Paste the entire signed message into textbox.)</li>
        <li>To set username, export and submit your public key:<br>
        <tt>gpg --armor --export [john]</tt></li>
